{"id":14881792,"mediaExerciseId":"f998b729-be6b-4959-8426-6be74c071e39","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":612473,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":739,"solutions":[{"id":5996376,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to determine if the company should pursue the international sales further or not.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":61,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/c2f07cc2e1269f46e3272272d5541f35/70ad4547d8002ac8afb231cd72d502b4/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/c2f07cc2e1269f46e3272272d5541f35/70ad4547d8002ac8afb231cd72d502b4/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Recall in the previous exercise, the projected gain from the proposed arrangement at the current exchange rate of $1.09/â‚¬ is **\\$ 931,950**. Since the company is gaining profit, the company **should pursue** the international sales further.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Since the company will pursue international sales, they will encounter the exchange rate risk.**Exchange rate** risk is the natural consequence in the international market where the value of the *currencies either increase or decrease*.  ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":136,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/c2f07cc2e1269f46e3272272d5541f35/e0f4cc10170cf8b3b406a3ed8ff6c5e7/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":69,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/c2f07cc2e1269f46e3272272d5541f35/e0f4cc10170cf8b3b406a3ed8ff6c5e7/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"One way to manage the exchange rate risk is through hedging.  **Hedging** is a technique to *limit the risk* of the company. To hedge the exchange rate risk, the company can enter a **forward trade**. A **forward trade** is an agreement to *exchange currency in the future*. The *exchange rate in the agreement* of a forward trade is called a **forward exchange rate**.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":181,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/c2f07cc2e1269f46e3272272d5541f35/1778f7e4c350f13c2d93a3ec5e3716d5/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/c2f07cc2e1269f46e3272272d5541f35/1778f7e4c350f13c2d93a3ec5e3716d5/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, the company should **pursue international sales** since it *increases their sales*. They can manage the risks of international sales by hedging.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/c2f07cc2e1269f46e3272272d5541f35/1542efa5bb4d6d1e92417c4fd3d1e5ed/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/c2f07cc2e1269f46e3272272d5541f35/1542efa5bb4d6d1e92417c4fd3d1e5ed/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"38b37559-31dc-460f-8f56-b7d6ce08427d","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29